STEP 2 — OS-LEVEL TUNING (Aura-1's kernel hardening)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Run as root. These settings persist across reboots via /etc/sysctl.conf
and /etc/rc.local.

2.1 DISABLE HYPERTHREADING
Hyperthreading adds cache contention between logical cores.
Isolate physical cores for trading — disable HT in BIOS, OR:
  echo off > /sys/devices/system/cpu/smt/control

2.2 CPU FREQUENCY SCALING — DISABLE P-STATES
CPU power management introduces microsecond-scale frequency changes.
  # Add to GRUB_CMDLINE_LINUX in /etc/default/grub:
  intel_pstate=disable processor.max_cstate=1 idle=poll
  # Then:
  update-grub && reboot

  # After reboot, set governor to performance:
  for cpu in /sys/devices/system/cpu/cpu*/cpufreq/scaling_governor; do
      echo performance > $cpu
  done

2.3 DISABLE C-STATES (CPU sleep states)
C-states cause wake-up latency (100μs+ for deep states).
  # Add to GRUB cmdline:
  processor.max_cstate=0 intel_idle.max_cstate=0

2.4 CPU ISOLATION (isolcpus)
Dedicate cores 0-3 to trading engine. OS scheduler won't touch them.
  # Add to GRUB cmdline:
  isolcpus=0,1,2,3 nohz_full=0,1,2,3 rcu_nocbs=0,1,2,3

  # In Rust, use taskset to pin the process:
  taskset -c 0-3 ./blink-engine

2.5 NUMA PINNING
Ensure trading process and NIC use same memory node (avoids PCIe bridge).
  # Check NUMA topology:
  numactl --hardware

  # Run engine on NUMA node 0:
  numactl --cpunodebind=0 --membind=0 ./blink-engine

2.6 HUGE PAGES (reduces TLB misses for large data structures)
  echo 1024 > /proc/sys/vm/nr_hugepages
  # Mount:
  mkdir /mnt/hugepages
  mount -t hugetlbfs none /mnt/hugepages

2.7 NETWORK STACK TUNING
  # /etc/sysctl.conf additions:
  net.core.rmem_max = 134217728        # 128MB receive buffer
  net.core.wmem_max = 134217728        # 128MB send buffer
  net.ipv4.tcp_rmem = 4096 87380 134217728
  net.ipv4.tcp_wmem = 4096 65536 134217728
  net.core.netdev_max_backlog = 250000 # Prevent packet drops
  net.ipv4.tcp_low_latency = 1         # Minimize TCP buffering
  net.ipv4.tcp_nodelay = 1             # Disable Nagle (set per-socket too!)
  net.core.busy_read = 50              # Busy-poll 50μs on socket
  net.core.busy_poll = 50

2.8 SOLARFLARE OPENONLOAD (kernel bypass)
  # Install OpenOnload driver (Solarflare NIC required):
  git clone https://github.com/Xilinx-CNS/onload
  cd onload && scripts/onload_install
  
  # Run engine with OpenOnload:
  onload ./blink-engine
  
  # Verify bypass active:
  onload_stackdump | grep "kernel_bypass"

