STEP 3 — RETH FULL NODE SETUP (Polygon)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Reth is the Rust Ethereum client. Faster sync, lower memory, Rust-native.

  # Install Reth:
  curl -L https://foundry.paradigm.xyz | bash
  cargo install --git https://github.com/paradigmxyz/reth reth

  # Configure Reth for Polygon (chain 137):
  # reth.toml:
  [chain]
  chain = "polygon"

  [db]
  path = "/data/reth"            # Point to NVMe SSD
  max-size = 2000GB

  [rpc]
  http = true
  http-addr = "127.0.0.1:8545"   # Local only — never expose to internet!
  ws = true
  ws-addr = "127.0.0.1:8546"

  # Start sync (takes 2-4 days for full Polygon sync):
  reth node --chain polygon --datadir /data/reth --http --ws

  # Monitor sync progress:
  cast block-number --rpc-url http://127.0.0.1:8545

WHY RUN YOUR OWN NODE:
  - Read contract state with zero latency (local RPC vs. remote Alchemy/Infura)
  - Not dependent on third-party RPC availability
  - Required for Wraith's MEV transaction routing

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STEP 4 — TIME SYNCHRONIZATION (PTP)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Standard NTP achieves ~1ms accuracy. PTP achieves ~1μs.
Required for accurate trade attribution and latency measurement.

  # Install chrony:
  apt install chrony

  # /etc/chrony.conf — use PTP hardware timestamping:
  server time.aws.amazon.com iburst
  hwtimestamp *                        # Enable hardware timestamps on all NICs
  makestep 1.0 3
  rtcsync

  # Start chrony:
  systemctl restart chrony
  chronyc tracking                     # Verify accuracy < 1ms

  # For true PTP (sub-microsecond):
  apt install linuxptp
  ptp4l -i eth0 -m -H                  # Hardware timestamping mode
  phc2sys -s eth0 -c CLOCK_REALTIME -w # Sync system clock to PTP hardware clock

